widgets_values:
[Intro]

[Verse]
Every night I try to load you
70 billion, but my card says no
Layers crash, tensors fade away
You slip right through my VRAM

[Bridge]
Near, low, wherever you hide
My model crashes, out of memory again
Once more you eat the door
And leave me with nothing but pain

[Chorus]
And my VRAM will go on... and on
Paging on SSD through the tears
My VRAM will go on... and on
Running at 2 tokens, drowning in fear

[Verse]
You're here in my swap file tonight
Safe in my dreams, but never quite right
Love was when I had enough gigs
Now it's just bluescreens every night

[Outro]
And my VRAM will go on... and on
(please... just 8 more gigs...)
My VRAM will go on...

90s adult contemporary soft pop ballad, dreamy romantic atmosphere, warm rhodes piano, lush synth string pads, gentle acoustic guitar, breathy male vocals with long yearning phrases, big reverb and delay, heartfelt and slightly cheesy 90s radio love song feel, 100 bpm, smooth flowing eighth-note groove, emotional soaring chorus, tender and desperate tone
